whitecat.core.agents
Class LocalForwarderMethodGenerator

java.lang.Object
  whitecat.core.agents.LocalForwarderMethodGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
MethodForwarderGenerator
public class LocalForwarderMethodGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements MethodForwarderGenerator

A method forwarder generator that works assuming that the proxy and the agent using the role are local each other. The method generated exploits a capability of the LocalAgentProxy that is an hashmap that stores references to the role instance.

Author:
Luca Ferrari - cat4hire (at) sourceforge.net

bindReferences

public boolean bindReferences(AgentProxy proxy,
                              IRole roleInstance)
                       throws WCForwarderMethodException
Description copied from interface: MethodForwarderGenerator
This method is called at the end of the generation of the new proxy instance. Place in this method code that serves for binding parameters used for method forwarding calls to the role instance (for instance the binding of a key in the hashmap for the references).

Specified by:
bindReferences in interface MethodForwarderGenerator
Parameters:
proxy - the agent proxy created from the manipulation
roleInstance - the role reference (if available)
Returns:
true if the bind has been done
Throws:
WCForwarderMethodException - if something goes wrong

Specified by:
init in interface MethodForwarderGenerator
